OL,3,COfcom to stop issuing phone numbers if
OL,4,Cisland law not updated, warns minister
OL,6,FA Jersey politician says the island
OL,7,Fcould run out of phone numbers if the
OL,8,FStates do not pass new telecoms
OL,9,Flegislation.
OL,11,FFor more than 20 years, the UK's
OL,12,Fcommunication regulator, Ofcom, has
OL,13,Fallocated phone numbers within the +44
OL,14,Frange to Channel Island operators
OL,15,Fwithout any legal authority to do so.
OL,17,FThe UK Communications Act 2003 allows
OL,18,FOfcom to manage phone numbers in the
OL,19,FUK, but those sections of the law were
OL,20,Fnever extended to the Channel Islands
OL,21,For the Isle of Man.
